Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.42,0:00:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Old man Kogorō is helping an old woman for free?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.58,0:00:09.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From what Takae Kiritani{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, an apartment landlady, says,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.19,0:00:12.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the old man visits her every week
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.45,0:00:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to help solve problems and neighbourhood troubles for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.62,0:00:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran and I couldn't believe it,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.96,0:00:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we decided to wait for him in Kiritani{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.01,0:00:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the guy who appeared was someone named Ryōhei Onda,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.75,0:00:27.04,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ryōhei Onda (21)\NUniversity Student
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.75,0:00:27.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,who doesn't bear the slightest resemblance to the old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.85,0:00:31.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He explained that he was the boyfriend of Kiritani{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s granddaughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.55,0:00:33.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and he was pretending to be the old man to go and check on her,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.25,0:00:35.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as her granddaughter was worried about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.13,0:00:39.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the case of the fake old man was quickly solved,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.16,0:00:41.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it was then that the real case began.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.97,0:00:45.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard sudden screams from the neighbouring apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.30,0:00:48.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I ran over, and the apartment's resident,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.29,0:00:52.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gensuke Denkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had bled to death,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.77,0:00:57.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the screams were from the other residents who found the corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.74,0:01:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time of death was last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.08,0:01:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the situation it was thought to be suicide, but no...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.83,0:01:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.08,0:01:10.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the killer is one of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.39,0:01:12.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the three residents who discovered the corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.65,0:01:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If cases were all men,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.53,0:01:36.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then I wonder if the unseen puzzles would be women?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.95,0:01:39.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even a fake Kogorō can have great deductions...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.37,0:01:41.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth behind the grim reaper case is revealed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.28,0:01:42.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.99,0:01:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.91,0:01:46.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.94,0:03:24.15,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Junji Hyōdō (28)\NApartment Resident
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.77,0:03:24.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, officers! Can we go yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.40,0:03:28.66,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kumi Ban'nai (22)\NApartment Resident
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.57,0:03:28.66,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You know that Denkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had to be alive to change the channel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.86,0:03:32.03,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ken Ishigame (64)\NApartment Resident
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.07,0:03:32.03,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Let us go back to our rooms already.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.03,0:03:34.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, but there's still the matter of the key...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.95,0:03:35.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who cares?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.75,0:03:39.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just got back from the hot spring, so we're tired!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.92,0:03:40.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So please...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.88,0:03:43.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's enough, you lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.34,0:03:46.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you interrupt someone when they're talking,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.63,0:03:49.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you're just trying to start a fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.38,0:03:54.10,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Takae Kiritani (70)\NApartment Landlady
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.63,0:03:51.68,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,If there's something you want to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.68,0:03:54.10,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,wait for them to finish talking first!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.25,0:03:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Clear a path.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.70,0:04:02.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what sort of police officers are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.22,0:04:05.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a great detective right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.92,0:04:07.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so why don't you ask his opinion!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.22,0:04:12.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.24,0:04:15.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You won't solve anything with such a conceited attitude! {query edit: s/by/with -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.35,0:04:18.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, wait, mum...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.46,0:04:21.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Mum...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.91,0:04:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah... I meant granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:28.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still haven't put together my deduction...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.83,0:04:32.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The landlady speaks loudly, doesn't she.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.01,0:04:35.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, a lot of old people do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.65,0:04:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't that because age makes them hard-of-hearing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.12,0:04:43.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seemed like she could hear us fine in our normal voices.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.78,0:04:45.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.69,0:04:51.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, some old people raise their voices to show they're still young and healthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.57,0:04:54.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.52,0:04:59.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it sounds like your phone's ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.66,0:05:03.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello? Hello...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.52,0:05:07.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's odd, nobody's there...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.55,0:05:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's an e-mail? Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.68,0:05:11.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.39,0:05:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, aren't you skilled, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.69,0:05:19.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had my granddaughter teach me how to use it once
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.69,0:05:22.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but can't remember which button does what.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.12,0:05:25.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you were younger,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.05,0:05:27.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you could've learnt to use it like you did a piano keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.32,0:05:29.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.22,0:05:31.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Piano?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.20,0:05:34.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An e-mail from her granddaughter, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.32,0:05:37.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No way! {"uso!" -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.28,0:05:40.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}'Thanks to my husband's schedule...'
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.50,0:05:42.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Doesn't that mean her granddaughter's married?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.54,0:05:45.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She even has a kid, and it doesn't look like she's a university student...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.50,0:05:49.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}which means that when this guy said she was his girlfriend...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.84,0:05:53.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}it was an outright lie! So then, who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.46,0:05:58.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was an e-mail from your granddaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.75,0:05:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, from her...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.79,0:06:01.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}G-Granddaughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.15,0:06:06.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But never mind that, about the zapping last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.35,0:06:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,do you remember around when it happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.76,0:06:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure... sometime around twilight, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.11,0:06:19.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when it happened, the channel changed several times quickly, stopped for a while, then started changing again?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.17,0:06:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.72,0:06:25.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I was sure it was some malicious presence from outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.92,0:06:28.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it stopped when I shut the curtains.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.27,0:06:32.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So it's just as I thought... I've solved the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.95,0:06:36.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the one who did it was likely that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.70,0:06:37.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But there's no proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.47,0:06:44.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If my theory's right, the killer should still have the evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.95,0:06:50.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, it doesn't look like they're gonna solve it anytime soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.92,0:06:52.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so why not...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.32,0:07:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,have the crimesolving pro, Detective Mouri, solve it for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.11,0:07:02.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.68,0:07:04.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.18,0:07:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, let's leave it all to Detective Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.51,0:07:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no... no, no no...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.87,0:07:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So how about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.82,0:07:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sleeping Kogorō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.89,0:07:21.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this was a murder, isn't it odd to claim that the killer is one of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.57,0:07:22.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.90,0:07:29.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you explain the loud noise we heard coming from the TV in this room just before we left for the hot spring?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.21,0:07:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just noise either, the channel changed too,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.46,0:07:36.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and he turned off the TV when we told him to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.18,0:07:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that proof that Denkawa was still alive then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.29,0:07:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Denkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s time of death was last night, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.96,0:07:48.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then there's no way the killer can be one of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.87,0:07:50.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,since we just got back from the hot spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.99,0:07:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to keep us here any longer,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.12,0:07:54.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then you have to solve those mysteries for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.87,0:07:57.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do your 'prideful deduction'!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.48,0:07:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still haven't yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.85,0:08:01.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.51,0:08:04.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if Detective Mouri can't solve this case yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.62,0:08:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we've got no intention of letting you three go since you're suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.66,0:08:13.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you three broke down the door, one of you threw the key next to the corpse
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.65,0:08:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make it seem like it was a locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.03,0:08:17.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,None of you are cleared of that suspicion yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.19,0:08:19.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that odd too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.95,0:08:22.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How come the police, who are always following Kogorō Mouri's instructions,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.26,0:08:25.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,are ignoring him this time round?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.40,0:08:30.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you brought out a fake Kogorō Mouri,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.84,0:08:34.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in order to put mental pressure on us so that the police can solve this case quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.93,0:08:36.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.57,0:08:39.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This man is the real Detective Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.75,0:08:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should we tell them that he's a fake?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.04,0:08:45.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we promised Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.22,0:08:46.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about the promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.43,0:08:52.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This guy saying that he's pretending to be my dad for the landlady's granddaughter was a blatant lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.96,0:08:55.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I don't know what he could be plotting!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.57,0:08:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.40,0:09:03.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, as you wish, the great Kogorō Mouri shall reveal the truth behind this case!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.55,0:09:08.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm? How interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.53,0:09:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no... that wasn't me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.48,0:09:15.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't get carried away just because you're pretending to be him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.13,0:09:20.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'll help you with various things, Uncle Kogorō!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.60,0:09:23.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.09,0:09:29.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just called the real Uncle Kogorō {s/phoned with/phoned/ alt "called" -uso.}\Nand heard the truth behind the case from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.07,0:09:32.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just go along with what I say, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.53,0:09:34.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.40,0:09:36.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.31,0:09:39.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll tell the officers to do what you asked!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.36,0:09:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.79,0:09:45.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, this guy isn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.62,0:09:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, you help out too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.82,0:09:50.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's lots of things he wants us to borrow and bring here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.13,0:09:52.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.67,0:09:55.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.58,0:09:58.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Because the real Sleeping Kogorō is right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.42,0:10:08.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, how long are you going to keep us waiting?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.39,0:10:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like you brought a lot of stuff into the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.99,0:10:16.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you use tools that were never in the room to begin with, you're not proving anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.37,0:10:20.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything brought into the room was already there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.19,0:10:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were just told not to use the actual objects for the trick experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.12,0:10:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's what the forensics officer who took the body told us, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.39,0:10:28.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Trick, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.55,0:10:31.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're still going on about that nonsense?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.54,0:10:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's your deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.80,0:10:37.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.56,0:10:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.18,0:10:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just tell them what I said and you'll be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.26,0:10:43.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Make it look impressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.99,0:10:48.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Act as if you were Sherlock Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.11,0:10:52.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.99,0:10:54.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Good evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.02,0:10:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is the 9 o'clock evening news for Monday, July 2nd!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.83,0:11:01.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who turned on the TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.83,0:11:03.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.56,0:11:05.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it certainly wasn't one of us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.87,0:11:08.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is still someone in the next room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.63,0:11:10.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.58,0:11:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you {\i1}can{\i0} turn on the TV if the timer's set...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.77,0:11:14.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What are you even saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.36,0:11:17.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And now, the third question!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.84,0:11:21.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hit! It's high! He's going for a home run!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.58,0:11:20.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's zapping!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.77,0:11:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What is going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.02,0:11:26.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There {\i1}has{\i0} to be somebody in that room!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.40,0:11:27.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.90,0:11:30.07,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's like a dream world...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.28,0:11:31.91,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Not even miracles are mysteries today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.69,0:11:34.66,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...and until the onions turn brown...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.35,0:11:36.91,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Higo scored right after the game started...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.66,0:11:39.00,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is a homicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.41,0:11:42.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a TV remote on top of the electric fan?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.71,0:11:44.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.85,0:11:47.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The channel button was pressed down by a clothes peg,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.79,0:11:54.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the TV remote was fixed on top of an electric fan facing downward!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.46,0:11:58.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as the fan moved and pointed to the TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.02,0:12:02.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it caused the channels to change, making people think it's zapping!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.42,0:12:04.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.08,0:12:08.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The TV was turned on by its programme timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.27,0:12:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was set to the news, it'd be easy to tell it's a live programme.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.61,0:12:13.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If after two or three minutes of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.80,0:12:18.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the timer on the fan had been set to make it move,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.75,0:12:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it'd sound as if he started zapping, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.42,0:12:24.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then how did the TV turn off?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.12,0:12:27.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We certainly heard the TV turn off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.58,0:12:30.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't it it have been done with the TV's sleep timer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.09,0:12:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.16,0:12:34.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the programme timer to turn the TV on,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.28,0:12:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the TV must've been turned off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.34,0:12:39.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if the TV was off, the sleep timer wouldn't work!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.95,0:12:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And how do you explain that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.05,0:12:43.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.77,0:12:45.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.93,0:12:51.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How was that done, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.10,0:12:57.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, as you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.71,0:13:02.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,another fan was used alongside the rotating one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.78,0:13:04.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the base of that fan,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.69,0:13:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a TV remote with its power button held down with a clothes peg was placed facing towards the TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.07,0:13:15.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and a newspaper flyer was placed in front of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.42,0:13:21.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if this fan's timer was set to start a few minutes after the rotating one,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.69,0:13:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the flyer blows away due to wind from the fan,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.23,0:13:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and since the obstacle blocking the infrared signals of the TV remote disappeared, the TV turns off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.44,0:13:34.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is how this was set up, making it look like someone had been zapping,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.84,0:13:39.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and turned off the TV due to the complaints.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.32,0:13:41.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how the flyer got on the bed!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.76,0:13:46.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, the first fan kept moving even after the TV was turned off,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.75,0:13:52.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the TV remote happened to be of the same brand as the landlady's TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.59,0:13:55.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so when the fan turned to the landlady's house,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.60,0:14:00.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it caused the TV in her living room to start zapping too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.18,0:14:03.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it wasn't the books on the table after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.55,0:14:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.44,0:14:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just the side effect of the killer's trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.89,0:14:09.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who set up this trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.96,0:14:13.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we came into the room, there wasn't any setup like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.69,0:14:15.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.17,0:14:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The TV remote has been stuck to the fan with plasters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.75,0:14:26.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall correctly, earlier you said you tripped and fell over the leg of the body, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.09,0:14:28.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What of it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.09,0:14:33.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you pulled the plaster off the electric fan, and stuck it on yourself...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.21,0:14:36.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I put on this plaster because a mosquito bit me at the hot spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.29,0:14:38.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I show you on the train ride home?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.13,0:14:41.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't mean this is the same plaster...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.26,0:14:46.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You stuck it on with a plaster because you thought that's what was used in the crime, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.89,0:14:46.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.45,0:14:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time between you breaking down the door, and turning the light on and finding Denkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body, was probably around 10 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.59,0:14:59.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's find out whether it's possible
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.26,0:15:02.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,for someone to restick plasters onto their body without being suspicious
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.12,0:15:04.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in such a small amount of time...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.08,0:15:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, Officer Takagi, I'll turn around for ten seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.58,0:15:10.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so would you try doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.71,0:15:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.11,0:15:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,10, 9, 8, 7,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.93,0:15:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1, 0!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.06,0:15:25.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.56,0:15:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, did you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.60,0:15:32.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not really... They're stuck on, but they're all wrinkled as I was rushing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.66,0:15:35.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe there was more time than that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.76,0:15:38.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ishigame{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took his time turning on the lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.08,0:15:43.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if there {\i1}was{\i0} more time, it'd still turn out the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.09,0:15:46.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've been dark before the lights came on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.76,0:15:49.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And from seeing her use her cell phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.93,0:15:52.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ban'nai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s likely right-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:55.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've been hard for her to use her left hand
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.60,0:15:58.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to neatly stick plasters on her right elbow and finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.92,0:16:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ishigame{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s compress is also firmly attached to his right shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.59,0:16:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although a compress and plasters could be used the same way,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.78,0:16:10.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it'd be impossible for someone to remove them
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.43,0:16:12.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and re-stick them onto their body so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.93,0:16:16.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, it'd be perfectly possible for the killer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.42,0:16:19.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to just crumple up and hide the item on themselves, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.42,0:16:23.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's unlikely that someone would do that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.93,0:16:27.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,knowing they might have to go through a police body search.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.41,0:16:32.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which leaves us with something that's {\i1}not{\i0} suspicious even when on a person's body,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.25,0:16:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and it's easy to retrieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.25,0:16:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hyōdō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the rubber band you used to tie your hair!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.93,0:16:45.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that, you could do it like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.75,0:16:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems to be holding it up well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.92,0:16:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to make it hard to investigate later, you tied your hair back straight away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.09,0:16:55.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.11,0:16:57.40,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's totally into it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.09,0:17:00.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a pretty good impostor...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.60,0:17:04.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. Since he's not sleeping, he seems even more like a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.41,0:17:06.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to complete the trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.92,0:17:11.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you entered the room, you had to remove all traces of the trick as fast as you could,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.42,0:17:14.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and retrieve the items you used.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.26,0:17:16.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, since you were the one who came into the room first
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.76,0:17:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to turn off the alarm...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.60,0:17:22.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You used the impact from 'tripping' over the fan
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.25,0:17:25.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to knock the remote away from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.09,0:17:27.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finally, if you squatted down to stop the alarm clock,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.76,0:17:32.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you could've taken the clothes pegs off the remotes without looking suspicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.59,0:17:37.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as well as grabbing the rubber band you used to tie your hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.42,0:17:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.10,0:17:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you actually {\i1}see{\i0} that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.90,0:17:48.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any proof that I used my hair tie to set up the trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.09,0:17:49.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.74,0:17:53.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh yeah, I didn't tell him that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.42,0:17:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, there was blood on one of the remotes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.00,0:18:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, as well as some traces of it having spread around a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.44,0:18:05.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, if the blood mark
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.26,0:18:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is from when the remote was attached to the fan,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.75,0:18:13.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the blood spatter from slicing Denkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s neck
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.42,0:18:17.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,should be on your hair tie, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.09,0:18:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hearing that, as if the channel had suddenly been changed,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.43,0:18:29.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hyōdō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} confessed to the crime, heartbroken.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.12,0:18:35.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It started when Denkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, fed up with Hyōdō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s phone constantly ringing,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.09,0:18:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,broke down his door and went into his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.42,0:18:48.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when Denkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} found that Hyōdō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had a case full of drugs in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.75,0:18:52.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that Hyōdō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was a courier for a drug smuggling syndicate,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.09,0:18:55.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Denkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} threatened him to hand over half of what he earned
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.61,0:18:57.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in exchange for not going to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.39,0:19:04.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hyōdō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} decided to kill Denkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, so an hour before the three left for the spring,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.42,0:19:07.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he got Denkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} drunk and killed him by slicing his neck with a kitchen knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.26,0:19:11.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then set up the trick, left the room, and locked the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.41,0:19:16.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After making it look like Denkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was still alive, thanks to the sound of the TV, he left to go to the spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.08,0:19:23.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finally, to stop the alarm clock he set up to go off right as they got back from the spring,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.75,0:19:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he broke down the door, threw the key next to the body, and disposed of the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.76,0:19:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.42,0:19:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And thankfully for the landlady,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.94,0:19:40.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she didn't find out this guy's a fake Kogorō Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.85,0:19:46.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, wait. There's still one person who's not quite happy with this...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.61,0:19:50.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.10,0:19:54.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to do by pretending to be my dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.42,0:19:56.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you already!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.76,0:20:00.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My girlfriend, the landlady's granddaughter, asked me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.09,0:20:02.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's bull! Her granddaughter's married!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.26,0:20:07.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It may look like you solved the case pretty nicely thanks to Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.60,0:20:09.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but you can't trick me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.09,0:20:12.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.47,0:20:14.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was your teacher, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.26,0:20:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That landlady was your primary schoolteacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.26,0:20:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.25,0:20:24.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite being such a kind person,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.58,0:20:28.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the landlady didn't help her husband with the apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.42,0:20:31.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,until ten years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.44,0:20:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so she must've had some other job before, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.43,0:20:37.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when I heard her scolding everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.11,0:20:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,speaking louder than normal, I thought it might've been a habit that carried over from when she was a teacher!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.15,0:20:45.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course... A teacher {\i1}would{\i0} have to raise her voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.10,0:20:50.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if she was a primary schoolteacher, she'd have to have known how to play the piano...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.11,0:20:56.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you were younger, you could've remembered it like a piano keyboard. {see 5:23.12}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.08,0:20:59.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.10,0:21:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...which she apparently does.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.92,0:21:06.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what finally convinced me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.76,0:21:08.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was when he called her 'mum'!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.76,0:21:11.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, wait, mum... {see 4:16.35}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.75,0:21:15.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For primary school students, their teacher's almost like a parent,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.25,0:21:19.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and some students actually {\i1}do{\i0} call them 'mum.'
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.77,0:21:22.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that sensation must've come back,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.76,0:21:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,causing you to blurt that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.26,0:21:27.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, how do you know all of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.75,0:21:31.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r} told me in an email!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.43,0:21:33.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You asked Shin'ichi about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.09,0:21:38.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'He was probably one of her granddaughter's high school classmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.77,0:21:40.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After hearing about the landlady's problems
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.93,0:21:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at their high school reunion three months ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.93,0:21:47.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he decided to pretend to be Kogorō...'
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.75,0:21:50.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I couldn't just leave my teacher like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.42,0:21:54.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, shouldn't you just be honest
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.42,0:21:55.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and tell her the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.59,0:22:00.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She yelled at me a lot to not lie,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.26,0:22:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so telling her the truth after all this time would be complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.43,0:22:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, true, you shouldn't lie, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.75,0:22:07.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're lying for her sake,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.42,0:22:11.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure she'll forgive you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.16,0:23:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A few days letter, we got a 'thank-you' letter from the landlady with a photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.08,0:23:44.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The letter said:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.08,0:23:47.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the apprentice you introduced me to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.75,0:23:51.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is a very nice young man, and helped me a lot...'
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.76,0:23:54.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't have any apprentice...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.93,0:23:57.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's still lying...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.46,0:24:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like there's a lot of beetles and stag beetles collected here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.70,0:24:06.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There you are, kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.72,0:24:08.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.09,0:24:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not a toy, don't touch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.04,0:24:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hang in there, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.79,0:24:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miyama... Stag Beetle...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.92,0:24:24.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan: 'Chase the Miyama Stag Beetle'
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.93,0:24:29.93,Signs,,0,0,0,,Conan\NEdogawa
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.93,0:24:29.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint, Oh Yeah: Name!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.49,0:24:32.59,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Alright, I'm catching beetles!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.59,0:24:33.25,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.25,0:24:34.55,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Then am I the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.55,0:24:35.13,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Good luck.
